# 🌲 Health Status Prediction using Random Forest Classifier

## 📌 Project Overview

This project demonstrates an end-to-end Machine Learning workflow using the **Random Forest Classification** algorithm to predict an individual's **Health Status** based on dietary habits, physical characteristics, activity level, and nutritional intake.

The project was developed using **Python** and **Scikit-learn**, covering every stage of a supervised machine learning project—from data preprocessing to model evaluation and interpretation.

---

# 🎯 Project Objective

The objective of this project is to classify an individual's health status into one of four categories:

- Healthy
- Obese
- Overweight
- Underweight

using demographic, dietary, and lifestyle information.

At first, the model trained got overfit. Analysis revealed that the model was trained, but the BMI feature dominated the model's decision-making. Therefore, the **BMI** feature was intentionally removed to prevent the model from relying on a highly correlated feature and to produce a more realistic classifier.

