# 🌲 Random Forest Model Training

A Random Forest classifier was selected because it is one of the most powerful supervised learning algorithms for classification problems. 
Unlike a single Decision Tree, Random Forest builds multiple trees and combines their predictions using majority voting.

Model configuration:

```python
rf_model = RandomForestClassifier(
    n_estimators=100,
    random_state=42
)
```

### Training Process

The model was trained using:

```python
rf_model.fit(x_train, y_train)
```

During training:

- 100 Decision Trees were constructed.
- Each tree was trained using a random subset of the training data.
- Each split is considered a random subset of features.
- Every tree learned different patterns from the dataset.
- During prediction, every tree voted for one of the four health classes.
- The class receiving the highest number of votes became the final prediction.

This ensemble approach reduces overfitting and generally produces better performance than a single Decision Tree.

