# 💡 Why BMI Was Removed

An earlier experiment achieved nearly **100% accuracy** because the model relied heavily on the BMI feature.

Since BMI is directly calculated from Height and Weight and is strongly associated with Health Status, it introduces potential **data leakage**.

To build a more realistic model, BMI was excluded before training.

The resulting model achieved:

**92.83% Accuracy**

This represents a more reliable estimate of real-world performance.
